figgy.title: Child works getting parent title when saving a source metadata ID
Order manager should have functionality to rotate images, and have that rotation show in the viewer.

comments.body: @kelea99 Was someone specifically concerned about this, or was somebody getting a bunch of images that needed rotating? When we've thought about this in the past it turned out it was really rarely a problem. Do you think we should close this until it happens?

hi, @tpendragon ! This has come up a couple of times. Most recently it involved an external scholar who provided us with photography that  she took in the field for her research. Post-figgy ingest, she noted that many of her images needed to be rotated. It would be helpful if this could be done by the scholar in figgy, so it would not mean that someone on PUL's end who can read the language (me, in this example) would be responsible for rotating and then a re-ingesting the images in figgy. Does this make sense? **Of note: I do not see this as a priority** :)
@kelea99 How was it handled this time? The studio just flipped them in photoshop or something?
@tpendragon, I rotated them in photoshop and cropped (if needed) there as well. they were saved and ingested again.
